<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="Liset" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">XS1721</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">XS1721</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">XS1721</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Class &apos;class&apos; cannot have multiple base classes: &apos;class_1&apos; and &apos;class_2&apos;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The most common cause of this error message is attempting to use multiple inheritance. A class in X# may only inherit directly from one class. However, a class can implement any number of interfaces.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Example</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following example shows one way in which SC1721 is generated, and then shows two possible ways to avoid the error.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// XS1721.prg  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class A {}  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class B {}  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class MyClass : A, B {}   // XS1721  </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// One possible fix is to use the following approach instead:  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class A {}  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class B : A {}  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class C : B {}  </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// Another possible fix is to use interfaces instead of base classes:  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class A {}  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public interface B {}  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class C : A, B {}  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
</topic>
